item.title: Rs model Header
item.dc:creator: @cartridges cartridges
item.description:
@cartridges wrote:

I suggest looking at the sourcecode for the RS Model Viewer. Although it only parses the “- 18” header, it still allows you to reverse correctly the fields in Model. From that, you can reverse the “- 23” from a knowledgeable context.

However, finding a way to see them in action is the best way to identify from this point on… There’s alot that RSMV cannot do, and does not interpret: For one it doesn’t understand how to read or map the texture mesh’s.
